node.text:
There is a version of you waiting to be accessed in the quantum realm of possibility. 

This version of you is more physically fit. More mentally equipped. More spiritually connected. More financially stable. More romantically fulfilled. It is a version of you that no longer feels alone, that feels connected to a living tribe of travelers on the Way. 

To become this future you, requires a simple choice. Say yes. The Fit For Service Fellowship will take care of the rest. This isn’t an empty boast, these are the words of the members themselves. In a survey 100% of all members said the following:

I experienced transformational growth.
I formed lifelong friendships. 
I feel more fit for service.
I would recommend it to friends and family. 

On top of that close to half of the members formed some new business endeavor, either on their own or with another member. 

The applications to join for the final trimester of the year are open now. The online programming begins in September and in October we are going to Sedona to meet with some of my own greatest teachers - to help us awaken the twin dragons of our masculine and feminine potential. If you are called, please apply. I look forward to meeting you in a few months!

LINK IN BIO

#fitforservicefellowship #fitforservice #community

node.title: Are You Willing To COMMIT TO YOUR POTENTIAL?

node.text:
Loving someone unconditionally can unlock their unlimited potential.

Imagine what we could accomplish if we loved ourselves the same way. 💙

Huge thank you to @robdialjr
for having me on the podcast. Link in Bio.

#practicenonjudgement #unconditionallove #bethechange

node.text:
Having a traumatic experience does not necessarily lead to being traumatized. 

It is not the experience itself but rather the judgment of the experience - along with any emotional associations - that leads to trauma.

From my latest podcast with @drdavidrabin. Link in Bio.

node.text:
We are of the Earth just as she is of us. Even when we fail to act as good stewards of her precious resources, she loves us unconditionally. Thank you, Pachamama, for all that you give, while asking for nothing in return. 💚

From my latest podcast with @erickgodsey. Link in Bio.

node.text:
Time, and the awareness of its passing, can eat you alive. It can lead you down the path of numbing, addiction, and despair.

Or... you can allow the understanding of life’s ephemeral provision to feed you, dancing with the gnosis that yes, one day you will die. And until you do, you are free to breathe, dance, play, sing, and bathe in the beauty of the Now.

From my latest podcast with @erickgodsey. Link in Bio.

node.text:
We all struggle dealing with the opinions of others. But guess what?

They don’t know shit about you. 

It’s important to realize that people’s opinions of you are merely fictional stories, seeking to confirm their bias of the person they’ve already determined you to be. 

YOU are the only person who can truly judge your actions.

Every month I do these zoom calls with the @fit.for.service Fellowship where people can ask anything that is on their mind to myself and the rest of the Fellowship. If you are interested in learning more about the program, check out the link in my bio.

#beyourself #youdoyou #ownyourlife

node.title: Do you CARE about what other people THINK

node.text:
LOVE is the foundation of any flourishing relationship. 

Yes, boundaries are important, but it is still possible to Love even with a boundary. Here are some questions to ask yourself to help determine whether or not to stay in a relationship: 

Are you doing your best to Love your partner? Not for who you wish them to be, but for exactly who they are? 

Or do you use love as a feedback mechanism to steer them in a certain direction? 

And is this partner helping you actualize my own potential and supporting me in my goals, or are they distracting and hindering you in some way? 

Relationships are great teachers. And remember, there is no such thing as a ‘failed’ relationship as long as you learned something. 

#sacredunion #relationships #love

node.text:
There is a version of you waiting to be accessed in the quantum realm of possibility. 

This version of you is more physically fit. More mentally equipped. More spiritually connected. More financially stable. More romantically fulfilled. It is a version of you that no longer feels alone, that feels connected to a living tribe of travelers on the Way. 

To become this future you, requires a simple choice. Say yes. The Fit For Service Fellowship will take care of the rest. This isn’t an empty boast, these are the words of the members themselves. In a survey 100% of all members said the following:

I experienced transformational growth.
I formed lifelong friendships. 
I feel more fit for service.
I would recommend it to friends and family. 

On top of that close to half of the members formed some new business endeavor, either on their own or with another member. 

The applications to join for the final trimester of the year are open now. The online programming begins in September and in October we are going to Sedona to meet with some of my own greatest teachers - to help us awaken the twin dragons of our masculine and feminine potential. If you are called, please apply. I look forward to meeting you in a few months!

LINK IN BIO

#fitforservicefellowship #fitforservice #community

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Aubrey Marcus in Austin, Texas. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'Aubrey Marcus @AubreyMarcus When a bone breaks and aligns incorrectly in your body, a doctor often times has to re-break the bone in order for you to heal. The same is true for the ego. Trauma or the conditioning of the world can cause our own mind to align incorrectly. Healing may require a breaking.'.

node.text:
This will be painful in the moment. But the benefit of healing correctly will ease your suffering for the rest of your life. 

It’s worth it. 

The invitation then is not to steer toward the indiscriminate destruction of all constructs, but intelligently targeting those areas that are out of alignment and allowing them to release, without fear or resistance to the pain. 

Only you know which parts of you need this. But a guide star is any area that obstructs your ability to feel love.

#healing #growth #enjoythejourney

node.text:
Can you be kind, even when they don't "deserve it"?

Can you trust someone even when they fail?

From my latest podcast with @daniele_bolelli.

Link in Bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Aubrey Marcus on July 14, 2021. May be an image of text that says '"YOU WILL NEVER REACH YOUR DESTINATION IF YOU STOP AND THROW STONES AT EVERY DOG THAT BARKS." -WINSTON CHURCHILL'.

node.text:
That person on Instagram. That stranger at the bar. The person in your family who always doubts you. 

You want to take the time and hurl your self-righteous stones at them?

That comes at a cost. 

Not only does it cost you time, you will have to simmer in the distemper of your judgment. It’s just a barking dog. If the barking stops, feel free to give them a pat or a hug. But don’t let yourself be bothered by the perceptions that live in anyone’s mind.

Artist: @ascendingstorm 🙏🏻

#forgiveness #boundaries #youdoyou

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Aubrey Marcus in Austin, Texas. May be an image of text that says '"WHEN |LET GO OF WHAT LAM, I BECOME WHAT I MIGHT BE.' -LAO TZU'.

node.text:
Your identity is based on the choices made in your personal history. However carefully crafted or randomly assigned, it is still a prison. 

Sure, the bars are malleable. Sure, others may be envious, judgmental, or in praise of your fancy prison. But the truth is that we are far more expansive than we realize.

We are not bound to our past. 

At any point we can recognize that we are the person who has learned from our history, and that person is capable of so much more. 

Artist: Martina Stipan

#beherenow #growthmindset #letgoofthepast

But deah has not touched you yet So how will you live while you still draw breath? Will you love? Will you feel? Will you be silly? Will you forgive? Will you do your fucking best? Or will you just complain about why you can't? Your choice.'.

node.text:
So what's it gonna be?

#powerofchoice #choiceisyours #mementomori

node.text:
“What are you afraid of?” the man asked his heart. The heart didn't reply. “There is no one out there that will hurt you, I'll protect you. I have grown strong, I'm a warrior now, you have nothing to fear.” Still the heart did not reply. “Tell me, heart. Was it our father? Was it our brothers? Was it one of our lovers? None of that matters now, I am a grown man, no one can do anything to us.” The heart remained quiet...closed.

The man grew frustrated. “Heart, you are a coward. Maybe you are defective. Maybe I just don't have a heart that works properly. No wonder I can't feel love.” The heart closed even tighter.

For months the man walked around, falling ever deeper into despair about his defective heart. Then one day the man grew very quiet. Quiet enough that he thought he could almost hear a whisper coming from his heart. He asked with all the compassion he was capable of, “Heart, what are you afraid of?” The heart whispered back, “You. I'm afraid of you.” The man cried. He had protected his heart from everyone but the one person that could hurt it the most - the tyrant inside.

#hanuman #listentoyourheart #stillnessspeaks

node.text:
Having a traumatic experience does not necessarily lead to being traumatized. 

It is not the experience itself but rather the judgment of the experience - along with any emotional associations - that leads to trauma.

From my latest podcast with @drdavidrabin. Link in Bio.
